featured_reviews.review_id:
Went to pick up my freezer, and it wouldn't fit in my car.  This was my fault and i asked if they could allow me to get my SUV and come back.  Keep in mind, when you do that, the ticket says you picked your stuff up.

I came back and called the number to let them know i was there.  No answer.  I happened to see a young lady who was doing the curside delivery, and asked if she could help me (i waited until she was done with her delivery).  She first ignored me and the pointed to a sign and said, "call the number or use the app."

I ended up walking into the store, finding a manager and asking her for help.  She then went to the back, found my freezer, with a note, and told them I was there.  Then the same girl came out and brought it to me!  Of course, with an attitude.  This was completely unprofessional, and I will never use curbside pickup at this store again.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Everything is good with Walmart except their frozen dairy department isn't kept fresh - especially noticeable by stale cheese that gets hard or goes bad very quickly after purchasing.

Just FYI, the milk and meats are usually okay because they get stocked directly from inside the dairy or meat refrigeration rooms, but the rest of the dairy department is particularly at risk because of the way it is stocked overnight without enough man-hours allowed by management to control and improve the efficiency of the cold-chain, stocking, and binning procedures.

If corporate Walmart sees this, I recommend diverting triple the number of employees of the usual overnight frozen dairy staff in order to maintain a complete 100% completion of stocking and binning every night within the first 4 hours before lunch and then sending all the staff from frozen dairy to other departments for the second half of the shift wherever it is needed.

That way, the cold chain is much more reliably followed and the perishable dairy products will be kept pristine and fresh for costumers. Not to mention avoiding items remaining shrink-wrapped on pallets night after night without being stocked or binned, causing the system product counts to be off or double ordered.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Wish I could give this store a 0.
The self check staff are always beyond rude, and just to get any sort of help is about as easy as getting water out of a rock.
The store was a mess, aisle full of racks and pallets.
I have not shopped there in months and after my last trip there, I  remembered why.
